    <title>To amend title 5, United States Code, to allow whistleblowers to disclose information to certain recipients.</title>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <updateDate>2019-02-07T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2019-02-07</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill modifies whistle-blower protections for federal employees or applicants who disclose classified national security information, or other protected information, that evidences wrongdoing.</p> <p>Currently, it is unlawful to retaliate against a federal employee for disclosing classified or protected information of wrongdoing to one of the following recipients: (1) the Office of Inspector General of their agency, (2) the U.S. Office of Special Counsel, or (3) a designated agency employee. This bill expands the list of recipients to whom a federal employee may make a protected disclosure to include a supervisor in the employee's direct chain of command.</p> <UL> <BR> </UL>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-02-12T21:15:20Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
        </item>
        <item>
          <name>Passed House</name>
          <updateDate>2019-02-11T13:48:07Z</updateDate>
          <versionCode>53</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2019-02-11</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill modifies whistle-blower protections for federal employees or applicants who disclose classified national security information, or other protected information, that evidences wrongdoing.</p> <p>Currently, it is unlawful to retaliate against a federal employee for disclosing classified or protected information of wrongdoing to one of the following recipients: (1) the Office of Inspector General of their agency, (2) the U.S. Office of Special Counsel, or (3) a designated agency employee. This bill expands the list of recipients to whom a federal employee may make a protected disclosure to include a supervisor in the employee's direct chain of command.<BR> </p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Passed House</actionDesc>
